Inter Milan CEO, Giuseppe Marotta, has confirmed the signing of Henrikh Mkhitaryan from AS Roma and Andre Onana from Ajax ahead of the 2022/23 season. Marotta also provided the latest transfer update on Romelu Lukaku and Paulo Dybala. This was disclosed by respected football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, in a tweet via Twitter on Monday. “We’re trying to sign Lukaku and Dybala, it depends on financial situation too. Bremer is a player we want, for sure,” Romano quoted Inter CEO Giuseppe Marotta as saying. “I can confirm we’ve signed André Onana and Henrikh Mkhitaryan on a free transfer, both deals are done”.